##**Images**
1. How to add images to pages
2. Choosing the right format
3. Optimizing images for the web

There are many reasons why you might add an image to your web page. You might want to include a logo, photograph, illustatrion, diagram, or chart.
1. The <img> element is used to add images to a web page.
2. You must *always* specify an src attribute to indicate the source of an image and an alt attribute to describe the content of an image.
3. Photograhps are best saved as JPEGs & illustrations or logos that use flat colors are better saved as GIFs.

