3. Background color

Colors can really bring your pages to life.
This chapter looks at:
1. How to specify colors
>Color Terminology
>Background colors for behind your entire page

Color pickers can help you find the color you want.
Color conveys mood and evokes reactions.

#**TEXT**

.Size and typeface of text
. Bold italics, capitals, underlines
. Spacing b/t lines, words, and letters
Properties that allow you to control the appereance of text can be split into two groups:
1. Those that directly affect the font and its appearance, whether it's regualar, bold, or italic.
2. Those that would have the same effect on text no matter what font you were using.
